<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Eustis</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-04"><hi rend="italic">September 4,
                                        1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 516.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of
                                your dispatch No. 358,<note n="1" xml:id="d287fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> of the 23d ultimo, inclosing a copy of a letter
                                from Mrs. Waller to her <pb facs="0343" n="283" xml:id="pg_283"/>
                                husband, the original of which was forwarded to Mr. Waller by you
                                through the foreign office.</p>
                            <p>The Department would be glad to be informed as to whether Mr.
                                Waller’s letters have been promptly delivered to him.</p>
                            <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>